 Unknown gunmen suspected to be kidnappers attacked an Abuja bound train on Thursday. The train left the Rigassa station at about 10 am in Kaduna before it was attacked by the gunmen at Katari, about 70 kilometers from Abuja. The gunmen attacked the train with guns and other projectiles. Confirming the incident to newsmen, a passenger disclosed that the train suffered “ballistic projectiles attack” but nobody was hurt. Details later…